A five-year-old boy was killed, and a 10-year-old girl suffered minor injuries on Friday night after they were hit by a car in Mayors walk Road, Pietermaritzburg. Mi7 emergency services was on scene. According to a statement by Mi7 national group, it is believed that the children were crossing the road when they were hit by a car. The driver fled the scene. “The five-year-old boy was declared dead on the scene and the 10-year-old girl was left with minor injuries and transported to hospital by another service provider,” read the statement.